{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:philemon.1",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "philemon",
    "chapterNumber": 1,
    "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1",
    "summary": "Source text for Philemon 1 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:philemon.1.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:1",
      "text": "Paul, a prisoner for Christ Jesus, and Timothy our brother, To Philemon our beloved fellow worker",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philemon.1.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:2",
      "text": "and Apphia our sister and Archippus our fellow soldier, and the church in your house:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philemon.1.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:3",
      "text": "Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philemon.1.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:4",
      "text": "I thank my God always when I remember you in my prayers,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philemon.1.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:5",
      "text": "because I hear of your love and of the faith which you have toward the Lord Jesus and all the saints,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philemon.1.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:6",
      "text": "and I pray that the sharing of your faith may promote the knowledge of all the good that is ours in Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philemon.1.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:7",
      "text": "For I have derived much joy and comfort from your love, my brother, because the hearts of the saints have been refreshed through you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philemon.1.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:8",
      "text": "Accordingly, though I am bold enough in Christ to command you to do what is required,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philemon.1.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:9",
      "text": "yet for love's sake I prefer to appeal to you—I, Paul, an ambassador and now a prisoner also for Christ Jesus —",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philemon.1.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:10",
      "text": "I appeal to you for my child, Onesimus, whose father I have become in my imprisonment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philemon.1.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:11",
      "text": "(Formerly he was useless to you, but now he is indeed useful to you and to me.)",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philemon.1.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:12",
      "text": "I am sending him back to you, sending my very heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philemon.1.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:13",
      "text": "I would have been glad to keep him with me, in order that he might serve me on your behalf during my imprisonment for the gospel;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philemon.1.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:14",
      "text": "but I preferred to do nothing without your consent in order that your goodness might not be by compulsion but of your own free will.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philemon.1.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:15",
      "text": "Perhaps this is why he was parted from you for a while, that you might have him back for ever,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philemon.1.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:16",
      "text": "no longer as a slave but more than a slave, as a beloved brother, especially to me but how much more to you, both in the flesh and in the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philemon.1.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:17",
      "text": "So if you consider me your partner, receive him as you would receive me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philemon.1.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:18",
      "text": "If he has wronged you at all, or owes you anything, charge that to my account.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philemon.1.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:19",
      "text": "I, Paul, write this with my own hand, I will repay it—to say nothing of your owing me even your own self.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philemon.1.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:20",
      "text": "Yes, brother, I want some benefit from you in the Lord. Refresh my heart in Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philemon.1.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:21",
      "text": "Confident of your obedience, I write to you, knowing that you will do even more than I say.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philemon.1.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:22",
      "text": "At the same time, prepare a guest room for me, for I am hoping through your prayers to be granted to you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philemon.1.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:23",
      "text": "Epaphras, my fellow prisoner in Christ Jesus, sends greetings to you,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philemon.1.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:24",
      "text": "and so do Mark, Aristarchus, Demas, and Luke, my fellow workers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philemon.1.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:25",
      "text": "The grace of the Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
